label chapter13:

    # [Scene: Flooded Dock at Night | Late Night]

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_1 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The low hiss of pumps, the occasional clank of tools, a far-off foghorn]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Rapid, taut percussion — propulsive, urgent]
    "You stand ankle-deep in cold, brackish water, the tide worrying at the stubs of pilings like a curious animal. Your field notebook is zipped shut against spray; your multi-tool presses warm against the slick of your"
    "palm. The irrigation rig — Elliot's midnight hack — breathes beside you, a tangle of reclaimed pipes, patched pumps, and a hacked controller with handwritten labels. It smells of salt, motor oil, and damp peat."
    "Elliot Chen leans over the console, forehead almost brushing the screen, fingers moving with the casual confidence of someone who has taught machines to be generous. He looks up when you breathe out; his grin is thin and rehearsed until you meet his eyes, and then it grows honest."
    show elliot_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elliot_chen "Ready on your mark. Two pulses, long and strong — it's supposed to shock the rhizome into faster cohesion. If it does what the simulations say, the panels will knit into a continuous mat in two tides instead of two months."
    show maya_rios at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_rios "And if it doesn't?"

    elliot_chen "Then we eat a lot of reputational dust and Luca sues everybody within earshot. But if it works—"
    "You feel your brother's absence like a new weight at your stern, a ballast of memory and duty. Risk is a ledger you have carried for years; tonight, you trade a page with someone else."
    "Sami Alvarez's voice drifts from the walkway, exuberant and sharp as a whistle in a storm. Neighbors cluster under patched awnings — a ragged chorus of headlamps and phone screens, hands cupping thermoses, sleeves hitched against spray."
    show sami_alvarez at center:
        zoom 0.7

    sami_alvarez "We can run this now. Noor says the soil temps are right. We've got rotation for the pumps. Maya, if the injunction comes from Luca, we'll stand in the way."

    maya_rios "Stand how?"

    sami_alvarez "Physically. Publicly. Loudly. Kayaks at the ready. We make it embarrassing to arrest a coastal grandma."
    "Laughter bounces off wet wood, thin and sharp. It breaks the tension into pieces you can hold."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Footsteps on the boardwalk; a polite but hard-voiced man in a rain suit approaches — Luca's liaison, tablet in hand]
    hide elliot_chen
    hide maya_rios
    hide sami_alvarez

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_2 at full_bg

    "Luca's Liaison" "Ms. Rios. Mr. Chen. I must insist you cease unauthorized engineering. There are liability concerns — obvious ones. The city will be forced to seek injunctive relief if you proceed."
    "You feel the words like a net thrown low across the water. They mean legal motion, lawyers in the morning, political leverage. But they do not mean the tide will wait."
    show elliot_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elliot_chen "We didn't ask for permission because permission takes a parliament of storms. We're not reckless; we're responsive. If the panels knit in tonight, the next surge won't chew the boardwalk like paper."
    "Luca's Liaison: (sharp) 'You are risking safety protocols and exposing residents to unknown variables. The developer expects compliance.'"
    show maya_rios at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_rios "We're risking everything anyway. We either roll up our sleeves or we lose more than pilings."

    "Luca's Liaison" "Then accept the consequences."
    "The threat hangs in the air and you taste it: metallic, adrenaline-bright. VeryHigh. The pumps wheeze as if in answer."

    menu:
        "Step forward to shield the rig":
            "You move in front of the console, shoulders squared, and start barking quick commands to the pump operators. Your voice carries over the hiss; people fall into the cadence."
        "Check the wiring one last time":
            "You crouch, palms working the clamped joints, thumb tracing a solder seam. The rig hums to itself like a thing being coaxed awake."

    # --- merge ---
    "The team prepares; narrative continues."
    # [Scene: Low Dock | Moments Later]
    hide elliot_chen
    hide maya_rios

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The first irrigation pulse unloads — a hiss, a heartbeat of water through pipes; distant thunder rumbles like a drumline]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Crescendo, strings and brass slicing into a bright, dangerous harmony]
    "You count under your breath and give the sign. Elliot's fingers hover, then depress. Liquid answers the call, pushed in a controlled, violent pulse that sends a bright smell of peat and nutrient up into your"
    "face. For a breath, the world is the pump and the pump is the world."
    "The living panels shiver as they receive the irrigation shock. Mud and root-tips twitch; hairline filaments of root knit together like hands finding each other. You can almost hear the plants rearrange themselves, a whisper against composite and mesh."
    "Farther out, the dark wall of the incoming spring surge swells. It comes faster than forecasts, a coat of water pressing forward across the bay. The crowd rallies like a single organism: voices spike, children squeal on clapped-together rafts, flashlights sweep across faces glistening with salt."
    show elliot_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elliot_chen "This is it! Second pulse on my mark!"
    show maya_rios at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_rios "Now."
    "He slams the control. The second pulse is longer, a sustaining shove of moisture and oxygen to the young roots. The panels flex as if sighing; where they join, the mat holds. A section — a"
    "stubborn, exposed seam that has threatened to peel in every previous tide — curls and settles. The water that would have pushed through finds a new contour, a softer line. Instead of shredding the boardwalk, it"
    "curls away, eddying harmlessly."
    "Sound explodes: a half-second of stunned silence, then a howl. Neighbors slap each other's backs; shoes squelch across the deck. Someone pours beer into a Styrofoam cup and offers it up like sacrament."
    "Elliot Chen grabs your shoulder, his grin big enough to be almost feral. His eyes shine with wet light."

    elliot_chen "Maya. You saw that, right? We did it."

    maya_rios "We did it."
    "A child's small hand finds yours. You bend down to steady them as they jostle forward to touch a panel; the child giggles at the tickle of a braided root. You look up and see faces"
    "lit not by fear but by an electric joy — a neighborhood that just learned a kind of power."

    menu:
        "Wrap your arms around Elliot, laughing":
            "You let go of the tension like a rope dropped into water. The hug is brief and solid; the warmth of another human pressed under the rain feels like a seal on something you weren't sure you could promise."
        "Push past to help secure the outer ties":
            "You shoulder into the work line, hands finding rope and knot. It's steadying — the physical effort translates triumph into something you can build on."

    # --- merge ---
    "The celebration and preparations continue; narrative proceeds."
    # [Scene: Flooded Dock at Dawn | After the Surge]
    hide elliot_chen
    hide maya_rios

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_4 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The exhausted buzzing of equipment, distant city sirens turned conversational, neighbors swapping accounts]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Triumphant brass over warm strings, underlaid with a steady heartbeat rhythm]
    "You stand watching the living spine settle, roots thickening where they touched, panels layered into a continuous line that breathes with the water. The victory is sharp and immediate: the models were right, the hack worked,"
    "the community held fast. Your chest feels as if someone has wound a spring inside it and let it go."

    "But the night left its calling card. Before the sun cleared fully, a terse email arrived on your phone" "Emergency review initiated."
    "Elliot Chen reads the message over your shoulder, then sets the phone down without a word. His hand finds yours and grips it — not possessive, but deliberate."
    show elliot_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elliot_chen "They'll try to frame this as chaos. But they can't un-see this night. People were here. People are safer. That's a different kind of proof."
    show maya_rios at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_rios "Proof people feel is hard to legislate."
    show sami_alvarez at center:
        zoom 0.7

    sami_alvarez "Look, the city can open all the reviews it wants. They've got a PR problem: a whole neighborhood now trusts this over a render."
    hide elliot_chen
    show dr_noor_patel at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_noor_patel "There will be hearings. There will be subpoenas. But there will also be data — and the data will be in our favor if we collect it. We've changed the initial conditions."
    "The world is louder now. Where once the sound of bureaucracy was a distant leak, it is a storm at the windows. But the sound of neighbor-voices — laughter, cross-talk, people planning next steps — is louder still. It is the noise of momentum."
    hide maya_rios
    show elliot_chen at right:
        zoom 0.7

    elliot_chen "You could have said no, you know. You didn't have to put your name on this."
    hide sami_alvarez
    show maya_rios at center:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_rios "I couldn't watch water pry apart the things we saved with our hands and walk away."

    elliot_chen "So... partner?"
    "You look at the living panels — at the way they tremble but stay, at the child's hand tracing a braided root. You think of your brother's face, the ledger of what you have carried, and you realize the accounting has shifted: risk shared is something different than risk avoided."

    maya_rios "Partner."
    "They cheer again, and you laugh with them, the sound a bright, splintering thing. There is pride, raw and electric. There is the sting of having provoked the machine of power. There is also, underneath, the"
    "slow, deep warmth of someone beside you who now knows what it costs to be you and still chooses to stay."
    "Luca's lawyers will write their letters. City Hall will convene reviews. The developer will spin the story. But the Harborfront's living spine exists now as proof that a different path is possible — messy, unauthorized, effective."
    "You have hacked policy by practice; you have opened a new question the city cannot ignore."
    hide dr_noor_patel
    hide elliot_chen
    hide maya_rios

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_5 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Distant applause like waves on stone]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Sweeping, triumphant; then gentle down to a warm resonance]
    "You close your hand around Elliot's, hold it for a beat, and then release it to the tasks ahead. Momentum hums in your chest. You are part of something larger than your fear. The route you"
    "chose was risky, yes — but it bought lives, time, and a community's confidence. That counts for something heavy and true."
    "You step away from the rig and across the slick boards, boots making small splashes. Neighbors call your name. Plans are already being sketched on the back of a soggy receipt. Sami talks about mapping tide-schedule"
    "rotations. Dr. Noor wants meter placements and longitudinal samples. Elliot hums through a list of grant contacts they can pressure with the night's data."
    "You let yourself feel the pride without apology. It is bright and a little dangerous — like standing at the edge of a new shoreline."

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Triumphant fade, then gentle closure]

    scene bg ch13_601bcb_7 at full_bg
    "THE END"
